1
00:00:02,609 --> 00:00:10,855
I remember myself, 
and at this time some 41 years ago

2
00:00:10,855 --> 00:00:15,832
going into a book store in San Francisco 
and getting one of those books.

3
00:00:15,832 --> 00:00:17,957
It was the third volume 
of the First Canto.

4
00:00:18,347 --> 00:00:20,606
[The Ultimate Question]

5
00:00:20,606 --> 00:00:24,116
I remember reading 
about Śukadev Goswāmī.

6
00:00:24,496 --> 00:00:28,095
And this is the time 
of the 60s,

7
00:00:28,095 --> 00:00:30,175
and Haight-Ashbury, 
and the hippy movement,
 

8
00:00:30,175 --> 00:00:36,389
and then, who is the leader?
A 16-year-old boy, who is naked.

9
00:00:36,389 --> 00:00:37,799
[Laughing]

10
00:00:37,799 --> 00:00:39,728
He’s walking around naked.

11
00:00:39,728 --> 00:00:43,607
Just he has long hair,
and he is naked.

12
00:00:43,607 --> 00:00:45,477
And when he enters 
the assembly,
 

13
00:00:45,477 --> 00:00:47,717
the sages give him 
the presidential seat

14
00:00:47,717 --> 00:00:50,941
because they can see
by the study of physiognomy 
 

15
00:00:50,941 --> 00:00:52,695
that he is not a madman,
 

16
00:00:52,695 --> 00:00:57,925
he is a liberated soul
to the extreme.

17
00:00:57,925 --> 00:01:01,326
So, and there is a beautiful description 
of Śukadev Goswāmī there;

18
00:01:01,326 --> 00:01:03,599
Gurudev used to chant it 
so many times.

19
00:01:03,599 --> 00:01:07,483
He liked it so much 
that actually some of the words

20
00:01:07,483 --> 00:01:09,832
he took from the descriptions
of Śukadev Goswāmī

21
00:01:09,832 --> 00:01:15,409
and used in his compositions 
in praise of Śrīla Guru Mahārāj.
 

22
00:01:15,409 --> 00:01:21,250
Because he is described as like
looking like Śyāmasundar Kṛṣṇa,

23
00:01:21,250 --> 00:01:22,749
the beauty of his neck,
his body …

24
00:01:22,749 --> 00:01:24,677
There is 
an elaborate description

25
00:01:24,677 --> 00:01:27,395
of just how beautiful 
Śukadev was.

26
00:01:28,225 --> 00:01:31,473
But so and I am reading
this book,

27
00:01:31,473 --> 00:01:33,270
and I had some other books 
at that time:

28
00:01:33,270 --> 00:01:36,930
Bhagavad-gītā, other things, 
but I wanted this.

29
00:01:36,930 --> 00:01:38,760
I always see 
in the Bhagavad-gītā purport

30
00:01:38,760 --> 00:01:40,253
the reference
to the Śrīmad Bhāgavatam,

31
00:01:40,253 --> 00:01:42,893
so I am reading this, 
and then it says,

32
00:01:42,893 --> 00:01:45,277
“Parīkṣit Mahārāj 
asked Śukadev,

33
00:01:45,277 --> 00:01:47,784
‘What is the purpose 
of one in life,

34
00:01:47,784 --> 00:01:51,824
specifically for one, 
who is about to die.’”

35
00:01:53,334 --> 00:01:56,049
The whole book, 
I am reading the Sanskrit,

36
00:01:56,049 --> 00:01:59,019
the Devanagari,
the words-for-words … everything,

37
00:01:59,019 --> 00:02:01,742
and the book 
leads us to this point,

38
00:02:01,742 --> 00:02:05,468
and the King says,
“What is the purpose of life
 

39
00:02:05,468 --> 00:02:08,833
specifically for one, 
who is about to die?”

40
00:02:08,833 --> 00:02:10,748
And I am getting more 
and more excited,

41
00:02:10,748 --> 00:02:13,865
then it says, “Thus end 
the Bhaktivedanta purports

42
00:02:13,865 --> 00:02:17,346
to the First Canto 
of the Śrīmad Bhāgavatam.”

43
00:02:17,346 --> 00:02:22,053
And I thought, “Oh, no!
This is unfair.” [Laughing]

44
00:02:22,053 --> 00:02:24,872
And I went like, 
“You are kidding!

45
00:02:24,872 --> 00:02:27,981
It doesn’t have the answer 
to the question.”

46
00:02:27,981 --> 00:02:31,755
I went back to the store 
and asked, 
 

47
00:02:31,755 --> 00:02:34,755
“Do you have the next book?”
and they said,

48
00:02:34,755 --> 00:02:37,269
“Oh, these are used books 
and we …” And I said,

49
00:02:37,269 --> 00:02:42,032
“Sir, you have to be kidding; 
lead us to this big question,

50
00:02:42,032 --> 00:02:45,428
and you don’t have the next book
that answers the question?”

51
00:02:45,428 --> 00:02:48,779
He’s like, “Don’t give me a hard time,
I just work here.”

52
00:02:48,779 --> 00:02:50,809
[Laughing]

53
00:02:52,929 --> 00:02:58,080
So I realized
that I would have to join

54
00:02:58,080 --> 00:03:00,790
[Laughing]

55
00:03:00,790 --> 00:03:03,966
to get the answer 
to this all-important question.

56
00:03:03,966 --> 00:03:06,106
[Laughing]

57
00:03:06,426 --> 00:03:07,426
And actually when 
I did join,

58
00:03:07,426 --> 00:03:11,018
they just published 
the first chapter of the Second Canto,

59
00:03:11,018 --> 00:03:14,439
where the question
“My dear king …”,
 

60
00:03:14,439 --> 00:03:18,860
I think, “Thank you, Lord!”
“… your question …”

61
00:03:18,860 --> 00:03:24,349
varīyān eṣa te praśnaḥ
kṛto loka-hitaṁ nṛpa

62
00:03:24,349 --> 00:03:27,349
ātmavit-sammataḥ puṁsāṁ
śrotavyādiṣu yaḥ paraḥ
[SB: 2.1.1]

63
00:03:27,349 --> 00:03:31,896
This question is beneficial
for everyone to hear.

